The South African Weather Service has forecast a drier than usual spring season this year. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Weather Service has forecast a drier than usual Spring season this year.The service says this is due to insufficient moisture in the atmosphere as a result of conditions in the Indian Ocean.Parts of the country have been experiencing rain over the past 24 hours; more downpours are expected within the next seven days.Weather SA forecaster Wayne Venter says, &quot;Rainfall is definitely in the forecast for the next seven days for the eastern part of the country.&quot;